To form a vector space, we only need to operation, addition and scalar
multiplication, only this, Itâ€™s enough, no inner product, no corss product, only
vector addition and scalar multiplication.<strong>It doesnâ€™t need to define
multiplication between two vectors, It doesnâ€™t define inner product, Thatâ€™s the
other structure.</strong><br /></li>
  <li>Why we define like this, to generalize, in this way, the polynomial is also a
vector space,too .</li>
</ol>

